translated: Öster, Karl-Inge, first doctor, Vadstena, b. 6/7/05 in Ore, Kopparb. 1st, son of Erik Helmer Bernhard Ö. and Ingeborg Märta Katarina Nordlund. Married 1934 to Margareta Linnéa Bengtsson. Children: Ingemar b. 1936. Completed high school in Västerås in 1924, graduated with a Bachelor of Medicine in 1927 and obtained a medical license in 1932 from the Karolinska Institute. Assistant doctor at Karlstad Hospital's medical department for six months (1932-1933), at its surgical department and acting third assistant doctor for one year (1933). Resident doctor at Marieberg Hospital (1933-1934), extra assistant doctor at Salberga Hospital (1934-1936), assistant doctor at Birgitta Hospital in Vadstena (1937), appointed as first doctor for a total of 2 years and 5 months. Became first doctor in Vadstena in 1943, appointed as chief physician for 1 year and 2 months, and as hospital director for 5 months. Acting psychiatrist at the forensic psychiatric clinic at Långholmen Island (1942-1943), acting assistant lecturer in forensic psychiatric matters in the medical board for 9 months. Consultative psychiatrist at the prison in Norrköping in 1946.
